  "local_port": 59758,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I deposit cash without cheque in SBI?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deposit cash directly into your State Bank of India (SBI) account without needing a cheque. SBI offers several convenient methods for cash deposits to cater to different customer preferences and needs. Below are the primary ways you can deposit cash into your SBI account:\n\n### 1. **Visit an SBI Branch**\n\n**a. Cash Deposit at the Counter:**\n- **Procedure:**\n  1. **Fill Out a Deposit Slip:** Obtain a deposit slip from the branch counter. Fill in your account number, name, and the amount you wish to deposit.\n  2. **Submit Cash and Deposit Slip:** Hand over the filled deposit slip along with the cash to the bank clerk.\n  3. **Receive Receipt:** After processing, you\u2019ll receive a receipt as proof of your deposit.\n\n- **Requirements:**\n  - **Identification:** For large deposits (typically \u20b950,000 and above), you may need to provide valid ID proof such as Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Passport, or Driving License.\n  - **Account Details:** Ensure you have the correct account number to avoid any discrepancies.\n\n### 2. **Use SBI ATMs with Cash Deposit Facility**\n\nSBI has equipped many of its ATMs with Cash Deposit Machines (CDMs) enabling customers to deposit cash directly into their accounts.\n\n- **Procedure:**\n  1. **Insert Debit Card:** Insert your SBI debit card into the ATM.\n  2. **Enter PIN:** Provide your debit card PIN to access your account.\n  3. **Select 'Deposit' Option:** Choose the cash deposit option from the menu.\n  4. **Insert Cash:** Place the cash into the designated slot as instructed by the machine.\n  5. **Confirm Transaction:** Review the deposit amount and confirm the transaction.\n  6. **Receive Receipt:** The ATM will dispense a receipt as proof of your deposit.\n\n- **Notes:**\n  - **ATM Availability:** Not all SBI ATMs support cash deposits. You can locate CDM-enabled ATMs using the [SBI ATM/Branch Locator](https://locator.sbi/).\n  - **Daily Limits:** There may be daily cash deposit limits per account. Check with your branch or refer to SBI\u2019s guidelines for specific limits.\n  \n### 3. **SBI Smart Collect Machines**\n\nIn certain locations, SBI has introduced Smart Collect Machines designed to facilitate easier and quicker cash deposits.\n\n- **Procedure:**\n  1. **Access the Machine:** Locate a Smart Collect Machine near your area.\n  2. **Follow On-Screen Instructions:** The machine will guide you through the deposit process, including scanning your debit card, entering your PIN, and inserting cash.\n  3. **Complete Transaction:** Confirm the amount and finalize the deposit to receive a receipt.\n\n### 4. **Inter-Branch Cash Deposits**\n\nIf your preferred branch lacks cash deposit facilities, you can deposit cash in any other SBI branch and have it transferred to your account.\n\n- **Procedure:**\n  1. **Visit a Different Branch:** Go to an SBI branch that offers cash deposit services.\n  2. **Provide Account Details:** Fill out a deposit slip with your account number and branch details.\n  3. **Submit Cash:** Hand over the cash along with the deposit slip to the bank clerk.\n  4. **Receive Confirmation:** Obtain a receipt confirming the deposit and transfer.\n\n### 5. **Through Authorized SBI Mobile Banking Agents**\n\nIn some regions, SBI partners with authorized agents who can facilitate cash deposits on behalf of the bank.\n\n- **Procedure:**\n  1. **Locate an Agent:** Find an authorized SBI mobile banking agent in your area.\n  2. **Provide Account Information:** Share your account details and the amount you wish to deposit.\n  3. **Hand Over Cash:** Give the cash to the agent, who will process the deposit.\n  4. **Receive Confirmation:** Obtain a receipt or confirmation from the agent for your records.\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n\n- **KYC Compliance:** Ensure your account is KYC (Know Your Customer) compliant. Large cash deposits may require additional verification or documentation.\n  \n- **Deposit Limits:** Be aware of any daily or transaction-specific deposit limits imposed by SBI or regulatory authorities.\n\n- **Security:** Always prioritize your safety when handling large amounts of cash. Prefer visiting bank branches or trusted ATMs with secure facilities.\n\n- **Receipts:** Always collect and store the deposit receipt as proof of transaction. This can be useful in case of any discrepancies or disputes.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nDepositing cash into your SBI account without a cheque is straightforward and can be done through various channels such as visiting a branch, using cash deposit-enabled ATMs, Smart Collect Machines, inter-branch services, or authorized mobile banking agents. Choose the method that best suits your convenience and ensure you follow the necessary procedures and requirements for a smooth transaction.\n\nIf you need further assistance or specific details related to your account or a particular deposit method, it's advisable to contact your nearest SBI branch or reach out to SBI\u2019s customer support.",
